The U.S. finally got a national bird. Government websites called bald eagles the national bird. Textbooks and newspaper articles agreed. But when Preston Cook searched high and low for any official documentation cementing the bird’s status, he found nothing. Flabbergasted, in 2011 he wrote to his senator — the late Dianne Feinstein, a Democrat from California — asking if her staff could investigate this mystery at the National Archives. “It turns out that the documentation wasn’t missing — it didn’t exist. We’ve never had a national bird,” Cook told The Washington Post. “The senator sent me back a letter saying it’s assumed to be our national bird, but it has never been declared our national bird.” On Monday, Congress made it official. The bald eagle will become the national bird after 248 years. Caption from article by Maria Luisa Paul.

Where did we get syphilis? In a study published Wednesday in the journal Nature, an international team studied ancient DNA harvested from lesion-ridden bones or teeth of five people who lived in Peru, Chile, Argentina and Mexico either before or around the time of Columbus. They found that early versions of the microbe, Treponema pallidum, that causes syphilis and related diseases were already diverse and widespread. Their analysis suggests that syphilis emerged in the Americas within the last 8,000 years and spread across the globe fueled by European colonization. “The syphilis debate was a big one, and it was a very emotional one ... a famous paleopathologist described it as one of the most enigmatic questions in science,” said Kirsten Bos, group leader for molecular paleopathology at the Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology and one of the leaders of the work. She argued the new evidence would settle the matter. “It’s a very clear slam dunk: Okay, this clearly came from the Americas.” Several outside researchers agreed the study provides valuable new evidence strongly suggesting an American origin for syphilis, but added that it wouldn’t close the debate. Understanding the differences between the subspecies that cause these different, but related, diseases is a key question for scientists trying to understand these diseases today. Caption from article by Carolyn Y. Johnson.

FTC MAKES sellers REVEAL “junk fees" The Federal Trade Commission on Tuesday issued long-awaited rules requiring companies to display the full price of a hotel room, concert ticket or sporting event up front to customers, rather than hiding any extra charges — often called “junk fees” — until the very end of the checkout process.The new regulations, which are slated to take effect next year, seek to crack down on “bait and switch” pricing practices, according to FTC Chair Lina Khan, who said the agency has received a groundswell of complaints about service charges, amenity fees and a raft of other potentially obscure, last-minute additions to consumers’ bills. The FTC’s rules still allow companies to impose fees, so long as they are clearly displayed.The agency also focused its prohibition on just the lodging and live-event industries, not the fuller array of firms — from airlines to internet giants — that have similarly stoked public anger.

Young adults are far more likely to approve of Luigi Mangione. The pollster YouGov asked a battery of questions recently about the killing of UnitedHealthcare chief executive Brian Thompson in Manhattan two weeks ago and the man who has been charged for it, Luigi Mangione. (Mangione was charged Tuesday with murder and terrorism.) Many people appeared unfamiliar with the story, offering no opinions. But among those who did, lots of young adults appeared sympathetic toward the alleged killer. And notably, they perceived those around them as sharing such views. The poll, which surveyed more than 1,000 people, showed Americans adults under 30 are about evenly split on whether they view Mangione favorably or unfavorably. About one-third hold each view. Adults aged 30 to 44 leaned only slightly negatively toward him. (In contrast, Americans aged 65-plus viewed Mangione unfavorably by about a 15-to-1 margin. Overall, Americans viewed Mangione more than 2-to-1 negatively.) Younger adults actually viewed Mangione more favorably than the man he allegedly killed, Thompson. Caption from article by Aaron Blake.

The Supreme Court said it will quickly review the constitutionality of the law that would to a TikTok ban. The justices said they’d consider if the law violates the First Amendment rights of millions of TikTok users and owners of the app.

Reality TV contestants may soon be employees. The National Labor Relations Board said this week that contestants on the show “Love Is Blind” are employees and should have the work protections that come with that classification. Once remedied, the case could become the basis for the improved working conditions that reality show stars have long awaited. After the agency worked with two “Love Is Blind” stars who filed unfair labor practice charges in 2023, the NLRB regional office in Minnesota assigned to the case issued a filing Wednesday. It said the hit Netflix show’s production companies — Delirium TV and Kinetic Content — had misclassified contestants as “non-employee ‘participants’” and found that they had required cast mates to sign participant agreements to discourage them from participating in legally protected labor actions, such as unionizing. The production companies and their former employees must come to an agreement on remedies due to the unlawful portions of the contract or meet for a hearing before an NLRB judge on April 22. Caption from original article by Samantha Chery.

A large number of mysterious drones have been reported flying over New Jersey and across the eastern U.S., sparking speculation and concern over where they came from and why. New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy and U.S. Sen. Andy Kim have both gone out on drone hunts, hoping for answers. The FBI, Homeland Security, state police and other agencies are investigating.

THIS Moon is Constantly ERUPTING No moon in our solar system is likely as chaotic as Io, Jupiter’s third largest. The rocky body looks like a pepperoni pizza because of the constant, numerous eruptions on its surface. The volcanic activity fills the skies with sulfur dioxide and is constantly changing features on the ground. It’s the most volcanically active world in our solar neighborhood, and has an impressive résumé for a place that is only slightly larger than our own moon.“Io is one of the most intriguing objects in the whole solar system,” said Scott Bolton, a director at the Southwest Research Institute. “This body is completely covered with volcanoes over both poles, all across its middle, constantly going off. So how does this really happen?” Io’s volcanic origins have baffled scientists. Many thought a global magma ocean may be percolating under Io’s surface, a feature that could have been common in the early evolution of planetary bodies in our universe and could explain the wide spread of volcanic activity.

Elon Musk has consistently been by Trump’s side this year. Whether the president-elect is meeting with heads of state, watching Ultimate Fighting Championship bouts or enjoying a holiday dinner, the world’s richest man is frequently by his side. The political donor’s many appearances and visits to Trump’s private Mar-a-Lago Club here highlight the unprecedented role the tech billionaire is playing in shaping the incoming administration. At the same time, he is acting like an honorary member of the Trump family as evidenced in this photo that Trump’s granddaughter shared on X, formerly Twitter. Meanwhile, Elon Musk’s net worth has climbed by more than $200 billion in 2024, a massive increase in the same year that the world’s richest person spent at least $277 million backing Donald Trump and other Republican candidates The bulk of the increase, more than $170 billion, has come since Election Day.. Captions from articles by Cat Zakrzewski, Faiz Siddiqui and Trisha Thadani.

Police in Madison, Wisconsin, are searching for a motive after a student at a private, K-12 Christian school in Madison, Wisconsin, killed two people and injured six on campus on Monday. The shooter is also dead. Police Chief Shon F. Barnes had said in an earlier news briefing that the shooter had killed four, but the department clarified the number in an update. Officers received an active-shooter report for Abundant Life Christian School at 10:57 a.m. They did not fire their weapons and found the suspected shooter dead, Barnes said. He said the hospitalized have injuries that range from minor to life-threatening. Based on reporting by Ben Brasch, Praveena Somasundaram, Kyle Melnick, María Luisa Paúl, Hannah Natanson and Nick Parker.

voice_to_text: this chick had rich girl problems her family had money beyond belief her father was a billionaire but her mother was a bit of a social climber from the time she was born Consuelo Vanderbilt as in the Vanderbilts was raised to marry the perfect match father William Kissam Vanderbilt came from a very wealthy family his grandfather was into railroads and shipping her mother Alva was a southern belle and she was dominating at the time the Vanderbilts were considered to be new money so they weren't accepted Alva tried desperately to be accepted by the social circles she was spending money on houses clothes parties but families like the Astors were considered to be old money and people like Mrs. Astor wouldn't let her in Alva realized she had the money but what they needed was a title the Vanderbilts had three children Consuelo was the eldest and the only daughter as a little girl she was trained to be the perfect wife her mother would make Consuelo wear a steel rod attached to her spine and neck to ensure proper posture it's never that serious she's growing up to be a gorgeous woman and she's rich rich so tons of men are proposing but Consuelo had her own plans she was secretly engaged Winthrop Rutherford was a socialite who was 15 years older than her but he didn't have enough money or a title so when a young Duke Charles Spencer Churchill came a knocking her mother was like bet now we get a title he was the ninth Duke of Marlborough and he had a palace but he didn't make any money so the palace was in shambles Alva was thinking this was a win win because now Consuelo would be a duchess and the duke would now be able to pay all his bills but our girl wasn't feeling it she refused so her mother locked her in the room and then her mother pretended to be very very ill so Consuelo was like alright I'll marry the guy they got married in a grand wedding so the dude got paid 2.5 million dollars which in today's money is $94 million as a married couple they would each receive $100,000 a year from the Vanderbilts which in today's money is $3.75 million she was a dollar princess this was an era when wealthy American women would marry European men with titles so they could exchange money for prestige she moved to England and the Duchess is adored by everyone because she was really kind and donated a lot of money together they had two sons John Albert and Ivor Charles but this was a loveless marriage and they lived separate lives a few years into their marriage she goes to her husband and she says look I'm getting back with my man Winthrop and the husband was like fine go ahead so she goes to Winthrop planning to marry him and he was like no thanks I changed my mind she goes back to her husband she's living her life she becomes besties with his first cousin Winston Churchill speaking of cousins she had an affair with another cousin named Reginald Fellowes and she may or may not have been slammed the clam with this guy an artist named Paul Helleu finally after 26 years of being in a loveless marriage they divorce and the marriage is annulled  the Duke gets married to a woman named Gladys Deacon this lady was an interesting character because she had a botched nose job and later she said Consuelo's second son with the Duke was not the Dukes he was Winthrop’s the scandal but our girl quickly got remarried as well to a French aviator named Jacques Balsan they had a happy marriage and were married for 35 years until he passed away in 1956 the American Duchess passed away in 1964 at the age of 87 when she passed she was only worth about $2 million which in today's money is about $20 million all of her Vanderbilt money went down to her sons

voice_to_text: please tell me you know who this man is he's a bit mysterious the utimate enigma considered one of the greatest songwriters of all time it's Bob Dylan 😎 there is a movie coming out about him a biopic called A Complete Unknown starring Timothée Chalamet who's playing a young Bob Dylan A Complete Unknown is diving into Dylan's meteoric rise between 1961 and 1965 I thought why not dig into the real Bob Dylan you know the one behind the harmonica and the poetry the one that dated muses got married in secret and pulled out a surprise divorce kid out of nowhere so buckle up buttercups it's about to get messy before Bob Dylan became Bob Dylan he was Bobby Zimmerman from Minnesota and Echo Helstrom was the it girl of hiving high school Echo was the blueprint of the bohemian type women that he would surround himself with later and many believe she was the inspiration for some of his early music fast forward to Greenwich Village in the early 60s where Bob meets Suze Rotolo the woman who will forever be immortalized on the cover of his Freewheelin’ album Suze was an artist and a political activist who introduced Bob to leftist politics which influenced his music in the film Elle Fanning is playing a character named Sylvie which is based on Suze can you see it their relationship was passionate but very messy Bob's career was taking off and he had a wandering eye enter folk singer Joan Baez she was already successful with her own album and she invited Bob to perform with her they started bumping uglies but soon he began to treat her like she was extra baggage she said he was demoralizing and they broke up later he apologized to her and they began performing together again I think we're gonna see this dynamic in the film as well by the mid 60s Bob's career is on fire and so is his love life enter Sara Lownds Sara was a former Playboy Bunny and a single mom they got married in 1965 Bob adopted her first daughter Maria and together they had four children three boys one girl Jesse Dylan who is a filmmaker daughter Anna Dylan who unlike some of her brothers is living more of a private life Sam Dylan who also stays a bit more private and then we've got Jakob Dylan also a singer and a songwriter lead vocalist of the Wallflowers who to me looks like a cuter version of his dad Bob and Sara were together for 12 years they grew apart he cheated on her they got divorced and Bob was doing his thing Bob was in a relationship with a woman named Ruth Tyrangiel this could be her or that could be her all I know is they were together for about 17 years and she was considered his common law wife here's where things get messy because around the same time he was in a relationship with his backup singer named Carolyn Dennis together they had a daughter they named Desiree and then they got married in secret no one knew about it until they filed for divorce no one knew they had another daughter Carolyn said they purposely left his last name off of the birth certificate so that Desiree could decide to add it if she wanted to later she also said that implying that he kept Desiree a secret was a huge insult and that he was a great father to her all I know is people have been obsessed with who he's dated some say Edie Sedgwick he denies it he had a thing with singer Nico apparently he asked Mavis Staples to marry him she said no he was a ladies man Bob Dylan is a living legend and I cannot wait to see this movie A Complete Unknown

voice_to_text: my heart felt physical pain watching this tears streaming down my face Super/Man the Christopher Reeve Story maybe I'm late to the game watching this 10/10 cannot recommend enough we learned about his parents how he grew up he went to Cornell then he went to Juilliard here he met Robin Williams they had a lifelong friendship boom he's hired for Superman the hottest Clark Kent he's filming in London where he meets Gae Exton they begin a relationship because his parents’ relationship was not a great example Christopher could not commit but he was living in London with Gae together they had two children son Matthew and daughter Alexandra Christopher is busier and busier doing Superman's 1 2 3 and 4 in 1987 Gae and Christopher decide to separate he moves back to the US and he sees his children on holidays later that same year Christopher meets a young singer actress named Dana Morosini they were a couple living together but again Christopher had commitment issues Christopher was Superman he was 6’4 buff athletic very physical he was a pilot he wind surfed sailed boats he learned how to ride horses for a project he was in even though he was allergic after about five years Christopher finally decided to propose to Dana and they got married in 1992 later that same year they had a son they named William in this documentary they talk about the tragic accident that happened in 1995 he was competing at a horse show when right before the third jump his horse just refused completely stopped Christopher was thrown off the horse fell directly on his head broken snapped just like a noose half an inch to the left he would have been gone half an inch to the right he would have just gotten up his first and second vertebrae completely destroyed his spinal cord was severely damaged he was paralyzed from the neck down could not breathe without a ventilator this documentary talks about how his own mother wanted to pull the plug and he wanted to unalive himself he didn't wanna go on any longer but Dana looked into his eyes told him she was never going anywhere and said you are still you and I love you listen tears are gonna stream down your face and then they talk about how Robin Williams went to the hospital to go visit him made him laugh the entire world wanted to know what happened to Christopher because he almost did not make it and with the help of Robin Williams and his wife and Christopher's wife Dana Christopher Reeve was able to make an appearance at the 1996 Oscars watching this reminded me to be grateful for your health for all of the little things does anyone remember this Super Bowl commercial from the year 2000 where Christopher Reeve looked like he was walking on his own two feet my jaw was on the floor and then come to find out it wasn't real it was just a commercial for some *investment* company I was bawling tears even looking at this I wanna cry Christopher Reeve was only 52 when he passed away in 2004 from cardiac arrest less than a year later his wife Dana was diagnosed with lung cancer even though she never smoked a year and a half after Christopher passed away Dana passed away leaving Will without parents at 13 years old this was so well done I'm still recovering his children are gorgeous and Will  is on Good Morning America to make your heart ache even more someone in this film says if Christopher was still alive Robin still would be too

IMAGENS IMPRESSIONANTES  A ponte do Estreito, localizada na divisa entre o Tocantins e o Maranhão, desabou neste domingo (22), provocando transtornos para motoristas e pedestres que utilizavam o acesso como principal ligação entre os dois estados. As causas do desabamento ainda estão sendo apuradas por autoridades locais. De acordo com informações preliminares, a estrutura já apresentava sinais de desgaste devido à falta de manutenção ao longo dos anos. PRELIMINARES As informações são preliminares e ainda não há detalhes sobre a causa e possíveis vítimas. Imagens registradas por populares e que circulam nas redes sociais mostram o momento em que a estrutura desaba e a situação em que ficou logo após o desabamento.  Testemunhas que presenciaram a cena trágica afirmam em vídeos gravados no local, que carretas que passavam sobre a ponte caíram dentro do rio.  Equipes de emergência foram acionadas para o local.  TRÁFEGO INTERROMPIDO  Com a queda da ponte, o tráfego na região foi completamente interrompido. Motoristas estão sendo orientados a buscar rotas alternativas enquanto equipes trabalham no local. GOVERNO PROMETE MEDIDAS EMERGENCIAIS Os governos do Tocantins e Maranhão já se manifestaram sobre o incidente e prometeu medidas emergenciais para restabelecer a ligação entre os dois territórios o mais breve possível. TRAGÉDIA ANUNCIADA Moradores da região cobram soluções definitivas para os problemas de infraestrutura da ponte, que já vinham sendo denunciados há anos, mas sem intervenções significativas das autoridades competentes.#ponte #tik_tok #video #brasil #CapCut #acidente

পছন্দের মানুষের অপ্রিয় হয়ে ওঠার ব্যাপারটা মনে মারাত্মক প্রভাব ফেলে। আমরা সকলেই চাই  প্রিয় মানুষের প্রিয় হয়ে উঠতে, কিন্তু তা আর পারি কোথায়। বরং একটু আগ বাড়িয়ে কথা বলতে গিয়ে তাদের বিরক্তির কারন হয়ে উঠি। আসলে আমাদের উদ্দেশ্য কখনোই তাদের বিরক্ত করার থাকে না। তবে কোনো কিছুর অজান্তেই আমরা ভুল করে বসি। কিন্তু তখন আমরা সেই ভুল বুঝতেও পারি না। আর পছন্দের মানুষটাও সরাসরি বলে ধরিয়ে দেয় না যে_ এটা তোমার ভুল হয়েছে, এখানে তোমার এটা না বলে ওটা বলা উচিত ছিলো। মানুষতো _ভুল হয়ে যেতে পারে, তা বলে দিলেই ভালো হয়। পরবর্তীতে তো আর এমনটা না করলেই তো ঠিক হয় নাকি? কিন্তু ভুলটাও কেউ ধরিয়ে না দিলে শুধরোবে কি করে? একবার হলেও তো বলা প্রয়োজন নাকি? অনেক সময় আমরা পছন্দের মানুষের মন খারাপকে ভালো করার জন্য কিছুটা পাগলামি করি। শুধুমাত্র যেনো তার মনটা ভালো থাকে। তাকে হাসানোর জন্য,  একটুু মনে স্বস্তি দেওয়ার জন্য নানান ধরনের উদ্ভট কথাও বলি, তাকে বোঝানোর জন্য অনেক ছলাকলা করি। এইসব প্রচেষ্টার মাঝে শুধুমাত্র লুকানো থাকে আমাদের মনের কোনে জমানো তার প্রতি মায়া,মমতা, প্রেম আর ভালোবাসা। কিন্তু এইসব প্রচেষ্টাকে যদি কেউ ভুল বুঝে, বিরক্ত হয়ে কথা বলা বন্ধ করে দেয় তখন নিজেকে খুব অসহায় মনে হয়। তখন নিজেকে বোঝাতে কষ্ট হয় যে _ আহা! তাকে একটু ভালো রাখতে গিয়ে উল্টো খারাপ হয়ে গেলাম। কি নিদারুণ দুঃখ যে হৃদয়ে লাগে তা আর কাউকে বলে বোঝানো যাবে না। পছন্দের মানুষটাকে আমরা একটু বেশি আগলে রাখতে চাই। কিন্তু আমাদের এই আগলে রাখতে চাওয়ার চেষ্টাতেই আমরা ব্যর্থ। আমরা তাদেরকে কখনোই খারাপ রাখার প্রয়াসে তাদের সাথে কথা বলি না। বরং তাদের একটু মন খারাপে পুরো পৃথিবী অন্ধকার দেখি আমরা। শুধু চেষ্টা করে যাই যে কিভাবে তার সমগ্র মন খারাপের অবসান ঘটানো যায়।  প্রিয় মানুষের মন ভালো রাখার প্রচেষ্টায় উল্টো তার বিরক্তির কারন হয়ে ওঠার মতো যন্ত্রণা বোধহয় তখন আর কিছুতে লাগে না #জামালপুরের_মেয়ে #100kviews #100klikes #100kfollowers🔥 #vairlvideotiktok #foryoupageofficiall #bdforyoupage #tiktokviral #tiktok #fypシ #pfyyyyyyyyyyy #foryou #foryourpagetiktok #vairlvideo #foryoupageシ #foryouシ #post #vedioviral #foryourpage @Tik Tok @For You @Bangladesh TikTok @TikTok Bangladesh

পর্ব:৮১_রুমাইশার মাথার ভেতরে রেড সিগন্যাল দিলো। মা কোনো একটা গন্ডগোল পাকাতে চলেছে, কিন্তু সেটা ঠিক কি, সেটা বুঝতে গেলে ওর বাইরে যাওয়া ছাড়া উপায় নেই। সাফওয়ান কে ও তো কিছুই জানানোর সুযোগ নেই আর! ফোন তো মা নিয়েই নিলো। মাএর দিকে কিছুক্ষণ অসহায় দৃষ্টিতে তাকিয়ে বিছানা থেকে নামলো রুমাইশা। তারপর দরজা টেনে ডাইনিং এর দিকে এগোলো। আয়েশা এলেন পেছন পেছন৷ ডাইনিং এ সোফায় বসে আছে শামসুল, তার বিপরীতে বসে আছে জুলেখা আর জুবায়ের৷ জুবায়েরের মুখে মিটিমিটি হাসি। জুলেখার ও তাই। শুধু মাত্র শামসুল মুখ ভার করে আছেন। ওনার মুখের অভিব্যক্তি দেখে বোঝার উপায় নেই যে উনি আসলে কেমন মুডে আছেন৷ রুমাইশা এসে দাড়ালো বাবার পাশে৷ জুলেখা হাসিমুখে রুমাইশার হাত ধরে বললেন, — আয় মা, আমার পাশে বস। তারপর ওকে হাত ধরে নিজের পাশে নিয়ে বসালেন৷ রুমাইশা খালার পাশে বসে বাবার দিকে প্রশ্নসূচক দৃষ্টিতে তাকালো একবার। শামসুলের চোখ পড়তেই তিনি চোখ ফিরিয়ে নিলেন। মেয়ে কে একরকম কথা দিয়ে আবার অন্য রকম করায় অপরাধবোধে ভুগছেন তিনি। বোনের সামনে কিভাবে গিয়ে দাড়াবেন সেটাও মাথার ভেতর ঘুরছে। জুলেখার থেকে তিনি যে রুনিয়াকে বেশি বিশ্বাস করেন আর সেই বিশ্বাসের মাত্রা যে কতটা বেশি সেটা শুধু তিনি জানেন। কিন্তু জুলেখাও হয়তো তার মেয়েকে অযত্নে রাখবে না! চিন্তায় কিলবিল করা মাথা টা ভারী হয়ে ক্রমশ নিচের দিকে ঝুকে গেলো যেন শামসুলের। রুমাইশা কেমন যেন সাহস হারিয়ে ফেলছে, এরা আসলে কেন এইভাবে সাজিয়ে গুজিয়ে এইখানে বসেছে তার কোনো আগা মাথা বের করতে পারছে না ও৷ আয়েশা শামসুলের পাশে বসে শামসুল কে বার বার ইশারা দিচ্ছেন রুমি কে বিয়ের কথা টা বলতে কিন্তু শামসুল অসম্মতি জানালেন প্রত্যেকবার। শেষে আয়েশা ই কথা টা তুললেন, গলা খাকারি দিয়ে তিনি বললেন, — রুমি, আমরা তোর ব্যাপারে একটা সিদ্ধান্ত নিয়েছি। তোর বাবা, আমি, রাফসান সবাই মিলে। আর যে সিদ্ধান্ত নিয়েছি সেটা অবশ্যই তোর ভালোর জন্যই। কারন আমরা তোর পরিবার। আমরা কখনো তোর খারাপ চাই না। আর পরিবারই একমাত্র জায়গা যেখানের মানুষ গুলো তাদের প্রিয় মানুষ দের কে সবসময় সবচেয়ে ভালোটা দেওয়ার চেষ্টা করে৷ রুমাইশা মনোযোগ দিলো মায়ের কথায় আয়েশা কিছুক্ষণ থেমে আবার ও বললেন, — তুই তোর জুলেখা খালা কে জন্মের পর থেকেই চিনিস। তোর খালা অনেক ভালো মনের মানুষ। আর তোর জুবায়ের ভাইয়া ও অনেক ভালো একটা ছেলে। সে বাইরে থেকে পড়াশোনা করেছে, ইঞ্জিনিয়ারিং সাবজেক্ট নিয়ে। সেখানে জব ও হয়ে যাবে কিছুদিন পর। সেখানেই সেটেল হবে। আর বিয়ের পর তোকেও নিয়ে যাবে৷ সে ছেলে হিসেবে খুবই উপযুক্ত সব দিক দিয়ে। তাই আমরা চাচ্ছিলাম জুবায়েরের সাথে তোর বিয়ে টা দিতে। মায়ের কথায় যেন রুমাইশার হৃদস্পন্দন থেমে গেলো! বিস্ফোরিত নয়নে তাকিয়ে রইলো ও মায়ের দিকে।আয়েশা কথা বলেই যাচ্ছেন,কিন্তু তার একটি কথাও কর্ণগোচর হলো না রুমাইশার।ওর কানে শুধু একটাই কথা বাজতে লাগলো, ‘আমরা চাচ্ছিলাম জুবায়েরের সাথে তোর বিয়ে টা দিতে’ রুমাইশার মাথার ভেতর টা ঘুরে উঠলো।কান দিয়ে গরম ধোয়া বের হচ্ছে যেন।অবিন্যস্ত দৃষ্টিতে বাবার দিকে একবার তাকালো ও,কিন্তু শামসুল নিচের দিকেই তাকিয়ে আছেন, মেয়ের চোখে চোখ মেলানোর সাহস পাচ্ছেন না তিনি।রুমাইশার মনে হলো যেন ওর চারপাশের পৃথিবী টা ঘুরছে। জুবায়ের!ওই লুইচ্চা জুবায়ের কে মা ওর সাথে গছিয়ে দিতে চাচ্ছে!মা ওর সাথে এইরকম করলো?আর বাবা?বাবা যে ওকে বলল সাফওয়ানের সাথে বিয়ে দিতে বাবার কোনো আপত্তি নেই! তাহলে এখন বাবা এইভাবে মাথা নিচু করে আছে কেন? এসব কি তাহলে ওর দুর্বলতার সুযোগ নেওয়ার জন্য?বাবাকি ওর সাথে বিশ্বাসী হওয়ার অভিনয় করলো শুধু!বাবা এইরকম করতে পারলো? আর রাফসান ভাইয়া!সেও এদের সাথে মিলে এইরকম একটা গা ঘিন ঘিন করা লুইচ্চার সাথে ওকে বিয়ে দিতে রাজি হলো!এরাই নাকি ওর আপন মানুষ!একবার জানার চেষ্টাও করলো না ওর মনের কথা টা!শুধু নিজেদের টাই ভাবলো!একটাবার ও সাফওয়ানের কথাটা এরা ভাবলো না!ও কিভাবে থাকবে সাফওয়ান কে ছাড়া!ও তো শেষ হয়ে যাবে একদম! ও কিভাবে বাচবে কেউ কি ভেবেছে? প্রচন্ড মনোকষ্টে চোখ থেকে দু ফোটা পানি গড়িয়ে পড়লো রুমাইশার।ইচ্ছা করছে চিৎকার করে কাদতে কিন্তু ওর গলা থেকে আওয়াজ বের হচ্ছে না!নিজেকে এই জগতের সবচেয়ে অসহায় প্রাণী মনে হচ্ছে ওর।কান্না চোখে আর ও একবার অভিমানী দৃষ্টিতে বাবার দিকে তাকালো ও।কিন্তু শামসুল আগের মতোই মাথা নিচু করে বসে আছে। রুমাইশার চোখে পানি দেখে জুলেখা হেসে বললেন, — আরে পাগলি মেয়ে,এইভাবে কাদার কি আছে?তোকে কি সারাজীবনের জন্য নিয়ে যাবো নাকি?তুই তো তোর বাবার মেয়েই থাকবি।এখনো বিয়ে হয়ে পারলো না আগের থেকেই পাগলি কাদছে৷ আয়েশা ও তাল মেলালেন জুলেখার সাথে।নিজের মাকে এইভাবে হাসতে দেখে ও অসহায় চোখে তাকালো মায়ের দিকে। মায়েরা নাকি সন্তানের মুখ দেখলেই সন্তানের মনের অবস্থা বুঝে যায়,সন্তানের দুঃখ কষ্ট বুঝে যায়,তাহলে তার মা বুঝছে না কেন?তার মা কি দেখিছে না তার চোখে ফুটে ওঠা অসহায়ত্বের পরিমাণ!

১৯৪৮ সালে ভারত উপমহাদেশ ব্রিটিশদের থেকে স্বাধীন হওয়ার পরে দুটি স্বাধীন রাষ্ট্রের জন্ম নেয় হিন্দুস্তান ও পাকিস্তান। পাকিস্তানের দুইটা ভাগ থাকে পূর্ব পাকিস্তান( পাকিস্তান ) ও পশ্চিম পাকিস্তান (বাংলাদেশ) । এরপর পাকিস্তানীরা বাঙ্গালীদের উপর শুরু করে অন্যায় অত্যাচার নির্যাতন, শাসন, শোষণ ও ধর্ষণ। ১৯৫২ সালে ভাষা আন্দোলন ১৯৫৮ সালে সাধারণ নির্বাচন ১৯৬৯ সালে গণঅভ্যুত্থান এবং ১৯৭১ সালের মহান মুক্তিযুদ্ধের মধ্য দিয়ে বাংলাদেশ প্রতিষ্ঠিত হয়। দীর্ঘ ৯ মাস যুদ্ধ করার পরে ১৬ই ডিসেম্বর আমরা স্বাধীনতা অর্জন করি। স্বাধীনতা অর্জন করে আমরা স্বাধীনতার স্বাদ পায়নি কখনো। কিন্তু ২০২৪ সালের ছাত্র জনতার গণ-অভ্যুত্থানের মধ্য দিয়ে ৫ই আগস্ট ফ্যাসিজ সরকারের পতনের পর আমরা স্বাধীনতার স্বাদ পাই।

voice_to_text: in my last video I said that it was hard for me to get into Drake because he keeps bringing up random people and places that I would never give a fuck about and I got so many comments that were like “you're just nitpicking Drake literally every other artist does that.” and I didn't really think that was true so I did what any normal human being who's unemployed and has an infinite amount of free time would do and I listened to four albums and wrote down every single time they mentioned either a person or a place first of all this is probably gonna be a long video so I'm gonna leave a time stamp here if you just wanna skip ahead and find out if Drake really does do this more than other rappers okay so the four albums I listened to were Chromakopia GNX Donda and For All The Dogs you might be wondering why Donda instead of one of the vultures and that's just because the vultures suck and I didn't wanna listen to em I also divided every person and place into two categories ones that I recognized and were explained and ones that I didn't recognize or were redundant one last thing before we start I'm not counting repeats as long as they happen on the same song if Tyler says hey Jane 15 times that only counts once but if Drake mentions Miami one time on six different songs that's gonna count six times chromakopia has a shockingly low amount given that two songs on there are named after people I only counted 16 instances and out of those 16 only two of them were ones that I didn't recognize and they happen in the same line on Ratatata he has a line where he goes “them boys went to Leuzinger i skated to Hamilton.” and I had to look that up it's just about high schools in LA obviously the average person isn't gonna know that so you know two for 16 is not bad and 16 in total that's that's really low compared to the ones we're gonna get to GNX and Donda both came out to 47 most of GNX's was talking about rappers like every feature on the album said their name at least once talking about all the members of TDE the people Kendrick calls out on whacked out murals that accounted for a majority of them and then with Donda it was mostly like biblical characters and stuff like that so I knew most of them for both albums G N X ended up with three out of 47 I didn't know and then Donda it was 5 out of 47 I didn't know both pretty good ratios  so far we have 16 47 and 47 add those all together it's 110 I want you to guess right now whether or not you think for all the dogs had over or under 110 I'm gonna assume you know since I'm asking you that it was over Drake had 153 instances of bringing up a random person or place on that album but what's even more absurd than that is that 64 of those were ones that I didn't know and I had to Google that's absurd let's look at the percentages on this and see how crazy it is comparatively two out of the 16 times Tyler mentioned a person or place on Chromakopia  I didn't know what he was talking about that's 12.5% for GNX it was three out of 47 that's 6% for Donda it was five out of 47 that's 11% for for all the dogs it was 64 out of 153 that is 42% of the time Drake mentions a Person or Place I didn't know what he was talking about that's absurd obviously it's gonna be lower for the OVO goons but for a regular person not knowing what Drake's talking about 42% of the time is crazy so yeah other rappers do it but nobody does it as much as Drake does
